steps.description:
Fix integer overflow in build_variable_domain (cpsat.rs lines 51-61). Replace the unsafe f64→i64 cast and unchecked arithmetic with safe validation:

1. Before casting, validate f64 bounds are finite and representable as i64:
   ```rust
   if !lo.is_finite() || !hi.is_finite() {
       return Err(format!("integer auto param {} has non-finite bounds [{}, {}]", param.id, lo, hi));
   }
   // i64 can represent up to 2^63-1 ≈ 9.22e18. Check f64 values are in representable range.
   const I64_MIN_F: f64 = i64::MIN as f64;
   const I64_MAX_F: f64 = i64::MAX as f64;
   if lo < I64_MIN_F || lo > I64_MAX_F || hi < I64_MIN_F || hi > I64_MAX_F {
       return Err(format!("integer auto param {} bounds [{}, {}] exceed i64 range", param.id, lo, hi));
   }
   ```

2. After casting to i64, use checked arithmetic for the domain size computation:
   ```rust
   let lo_i = lo as i64;
   let hi_i = hi as i64;
   let size = hi_i.checked_sub(lo_i)
       .and_then(|d| d.checked_add(1))
       .unwrap_or(i64::MAX);
   ```

3. Keep the existing `size > MAX_INT_DOMAIN || size <= 0` guard, which now safely handles any result.

Verify all existing integer tests still pass AND all new step-19 overflow tests pass without panicking. Run `cargo test -p reify-constraints`.
